      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>ACM’s consolidated article template, introduced in 2017, provides a consistent
      <Span xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
         id="ID.074"
         actualtext="LaTeX"
         phoneme="[ˈlaːtɛx]"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>LATEX
      </Span>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>style for useacross ACM publications, and incorporates accessibility and metadata-extraction functionalitynecessary for future Digital Library endeavors. Numerous ACM and SIG-specific
      <Span xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
         id="ID.075"
         actualtext="LaTeX"
         phoneme="[ˈlaːtɛx]"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>LATEX
      </Span>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>templateshave been examined, and their unique features incorporated into this single new template.
